#. [part]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:6
msgid "Excerpt from a journal at the Great Library:"
msgstr "Extracto de un diario de la Gran Biblioteca:"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:12
msgid ""
"Hello, respected reader, I do not know how you got your hands on this "
"journal, but I am glad you did. This is a life-changing story for me and I "
"wish to share it with you. Before we can being, I have to give you a lesson "
"in history. These account of events have been passed down in our village "
"from generation to generation. This chronicle of events is called the First "
"Elemental War and we have been told that we must never forget it."
msgstr ""
"Hola, respetado lector. No sé cómo llegó este diario a sus manos, pero me "
"alegra que así sea. Esta es una historia que cambió mi vida y quiero "
"compartirla contigo. Antes de empezar, tengo que darte una pequeña lección "
"de historia. Estos eventos se han transmitido de generación en generación en "
"nuestro pueblo. La crónica se conoce como la Primera Guerra Elemental y "
"siempre nos han dicho que nunca debemos olvidarla."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:14
msgid ""
"The First Elemental War took place several centuries ago, a cataclysmic war "
"that had erupted throughout the known continents of Irdya. The forces of the "
"Dark Elementalist, a sorcerer with unrivaled mastery of all magic, wished to "
"extinguish all life from Irdya and had unleased his endless legions of "
"undead and elementals on the world. His will and power had been opposed by "
"the combined alliance of the world's races including ours, the Aragwaithi."
msgstr ""
"La Primera Guerra Elemental ocurrió hace varios siglos. Fue una guerra "
"cataclísmica que estalló en todos los continentes conocidos de Irdya. Las "
"fuerzas del Elementalista Oscuro, un hechicero con dominio absoluto de toda "
"la magia, querían extinguir toda vida en Irdya y desató sus interminables "
"legiones de no muertos y elementales sobre el mundo. Su voluntad y poder "
"fueron enfrentados por la alianza combinada de todas las razas del mundo, "
"incluidos los nuestros: los Aragwaithi."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The war went on for almost a century until it finally concluded. The "
"immortal evil was sealed away and the world could rebuild from the ashes. "
"The Aragwaithi then founded their Great Kingdom at Northwestern Argea, which "
"some called the Old Continent. Centuries have passed and the Aragwaithi grew "
"to be the most noble, organised, and stable of all the world's races."
msgstr ""
"La guerra duró casi un siglo hasta que finalmente terminó. El mal inmortal "
"fue sellado y el mundo pudo reconstruirse de las cenizas. Los Aragwaithi "
"fundaron entonces su Gran Reino en el noroeste de Argea, al que algunos "
"llaman el Continente Antiguo. Han pasado siglos y los Aragwaithi se han "
"convertido en la raza más noble, organizada y estable de todo el mundo."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Now, we can get back into my story. You might be wondering how does all this "
"relates to our village? Well, I shall disclose the information. Our village "
"founder, Miyamura, had been a hero of the First Elemental War and his "
"greatest feat was the demise of the Great Lightning Dragon. The Aragwaith "
"Great Sorceresses of that time had imbued the dragon's essence in his sword "
"allowing it to harness the lightning itself."
msgstr ""
"Ahora sí puedo volver a mi historia. Tal vez te preguntes qué tiene que ver "
"todo esto con nuestro pueblo. Te lo contaré. El fundador de nuestro pueblo, "
"Miyamura, fue un héroe de la Primera Guerra Elemental y su mayor hazaña fue "
"acabar con el Gran Dragón del Relámpago. Las grandes Hechiceras Aragwaithi "
"de aquella época impregnaron la esencia del dragón en su espada, "
"permitiéndole dominar el propio relámpago."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Now, this sword, known as the <i>Electrifyre</i> now rests in the shrine "
"just outside our village and it is our sworn duty as the Aragwaithi to watch "
"over, protect and never allow it to fall into the wrong hands."
msgstr ""
"Ahora esa espada, conocida como <i>Electrifyre</i>, descansa en el santuario "
"justo fuera de nuestro pueblo y es nuestro deber jurado como Aragwaithi "
"vigilarla, protegerla y nunca permitir que caiga en las manos equivocadas."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The lands of the Aragwaithi have been mostly peaceful and the sword had not "
"been in danger any time save for that one time..."
msgstr ""
"Las tierras de los Aragwaithi han sido mayormente pacíficas y la espada "
"nunca había estado en peligro… salvo aquella única vez…"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:28
msgid ""
"I should tell you something about myself as we progress further into the "
"story. I was given the name Hikaru and I descend from the line of Miyamura "
"himself. As such, I had been brought up as a swordsman in the Aragwaithian "
"way of tradition and honor."
msgstr ""
"Debería contarte algo sobre mí mientras avanzamos en la historia. Me "
"pusieron el nombre Hikaru y desciendo directamente de la línea de Miyamura. "
"Por eso me criaron como espadachín siguiendo la tradición y el honor "
"Aragwaithiano."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:30
msgid ""
"During my training at the city of Aeranas, I sometimes used to listen to the "
"bards at the city square to learn of the tales of the modern heroes of our "
"people. The Aragwaith-Dunefolk war was going on at the time, so the bards "
"had plenty of stories to sing and exaggerate. One such individual stood out "
"from the rest: Ryuuma Shimotsuki."
msgstr ""
"Durante mi entrenamiento en la ciudad de Aeranas, a veces escuchaba a los "
"bardos en la plaza para conocer las hazañas de los héroes modernos de "
"nuestro pueblo. En esa época estaba en curso la guerra entre Aragwaithi y "
"barjanes, así que los bardos tenían muchas historias que cantar (y "
"exagerar). Uno de ellos destacaba por encima del resto: Ryuuma Shimotsuki."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:32
msgid ""
"He hailed from a town at the southern region, one of the towns that had been "
"caught in the crossfire during the early stages of the war. Having narrowly "
"escaped death, and the sole survivor of his family, Ryuuma had enlisted and "
"trained ceaselessly to become a warrior."
msgstr ""
"Provenía de un pueblo en la región sur, uno de los tantos que quedaron "
"atrapados en el fuego cruzado durante las primeras etapas de la guerra. Tras "
"escapar por poco de la muerte y ser el único sobreviviente de su familia, "
"Ryuuma se alistó y entrenó sin descanso para convertirse en guerrero."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:36
msgid ""
"During his first mission and every mission henceforth, Ryuuma proved his "
"skills in battle, besting any foe that crossed blades with him or conquering "
"any beast that challenged him. His greatest feat was during the climax of "
"the war where he fought in the frontlines and battled his way through to the "
"current Great Sultan and forced his surrendered. The war had finally ended "
"and he had been declared a hero by the Crown Prince."
msgstr ""
"En su primera misión y en todas las siguientes, Ryuuma demostró su habilidad "
"en combate: vencía a cualquier enemigo que cruzara espadas con él y "
"derrotaba a cualquier bestia que lo desafiara. Su mayor hazaña ocurrió en el "
"clímax de la guerra, cuando luchó en primera línea, se abrió paso hasta el "
"Gran Sultán actual y lo obligó a rendirse. La guerra terminó al fin y el "
"príncipe heredero lo declaró héroe."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:38
msgid ""
"After my training had been completed, I returned to the village and was "
"appointed as the militia captain. The guarding of the village and its shrine "
"has been mostly uneventful save for the occassional wild beast and ogres. I "
"really longed to have an adventure of my own, an adventure of going to "
"exotic places, battling extraordinary, having a tale worth telling by bards "
"through out the Kingdom."
msgstr ""
"Una vez terminado mi entrenamiento, regresé al pueblo y me nombraron capitán "
"de la milicia. Proteger el pueblo y su santuario había sido casi siempre "
"tranquilo, salvo por alguna bestia salvaje o algún ogro de vez en cuando. Yo "
"realmente anhelaba tener mi propia aventura: viajar a lugares exóticos, "
"combatir lo extraordinario y vivir una historia que valiera la pena ser "
"cantada por los bardos en todo el Reino."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:40
msgid ""
"Maybe this current retrieval quest for the Electrifyre can be such as this? "
"These mages had stolen our village's most sacred treasure. This did not bode "
"well with the village. We mounted a raiding party immediately for the sole "
"intent of bringing it back."
msgstr ""
"¿Y si esta misión para recuperar la Electryfire era exactamente eso? Esos "
"magos habían robado el tesoro más sagrado de nuestro pueblo. El pueblo no "
"podía aceptarlo. Formamos de inmediato un grupo de asalto con el único "
"objetivo de traerla de vuelta."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:42
msgid ""
"The mage, on interrogation, had revealed it was being taken to a fortress to "
"the South, and this was the only clue. We have strided southwards for an "
"entire day, having arrived at a hilly region at the Wild Lands..."
msgstr ""
"Bajo interrogatorio, el mago reveló que la llevaban a una fortaleza más al "
"sur. Esa era la única pista. Marchamos hacia el sur durante un día entero y "
"llegamos a una región de colinas en las Tierras Salvajes…"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:48
msgid ""
"After assisting the Scholar Ayanami and acquiring the support of her adepts, "
"we persisted our march further southwards. By now, we had ventured further "
"than we had ever gone before and had entered into unknown territory."
msgstr ""
"Tras ayudar a la erudita Ayanami y conseguir el apoyo de sus adeptas, "
"seguimos marchando más al sur. Para entonces ya habíamos avanzado más lejos "
"que nunca y habíamos entrado en territorio desconocido."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:51
msgid ""
"Before the first skirmish, we had sent a scout to the Perch to enlist the "
"aid of the Eagle Riders. I really hope they would arrive soon to aid our "
"quest."
msgstr ""
"Antes del primer enfrentamiento, enviamos un explorador al Percha para pedir "
"la ayuda de los jinetes de águila. Espero de verdad que lleguen pronto a "
"apoyarnos."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:59
msgid ""
"The vampires are an ancient race, having existed since the First Age. How "
"they came to exist is lost knowledge. Once, they had fought alongside our "
"people during the First Elemental War but as the centuries passed, their "
"Monarchy decided to not hold the alliance anymore and we have not been at "
"the best of terms since then."
msgstr ""
"Los vampiros son una raza antigua que existe desde la Primera Era. Cómo "
"llegaron a existir es un conocimiento perdido. En el pasado lucharon junto a "
"nuestro pueblo durante la Primera Guerra Elemental, pero con el paso de los "
"siglos su monarquía decidió romper la alianza y desde entonces no tenemos "
"las mejores relaciones."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:61
msgid ""
"The vampires had proved themselves to be challenging adversaries during the "
"night, only allowing us to gain ground during the day time. Such an "
"experience reminded me of the legend of an aragwaithi captain who had become "
"a vampire by drinking vampiric blood out of the desire to keep on existing. "
"He was once the commanding officer of Ryuuma Shimotsuki. This commander used "
"his vampiric powers to terrorise the vanguard of the Dunefolk of the war, "
"and initially drove them back."
msgstr ""
"Los vampiros resultaron ser enemigos muy difíciles durante la noche; solo "
"podíamos avanzar de día. Esa experiencia me recordó la leyenda de un capitán "
"Aragwaith que se convirtió en vampiro al beber sangre vampírica por el deseo "
"de seguir viviendo. Ese capitán había sido el superior de Ryuuma Shimotsuki. "
"Con sus poderes vampíricos aterrorizó la vanguardia de los barjanes y al "
"principio los hizo retroceder."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:63
msgid ""
"However, his transformation was exposed at the heat of battle and his own "
"unit turned on him. The bards did not mention if he was executed or exiled "
"but after his forced resignation, Ryuuma was appointed as the captain of the "
"unit. It was an interesting twist to his heroic exploits during the war."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, su transformación fue descubierta en pleno combate y su propia "
"unidad se volvió en su contra. Los bardos no cuentan si lo ejecutaron o lo "
"exiliaron, pero tras su destitución forzada, Ryuuma fue nombrado capitán de "
"la unidad. Fue un giro interesante en sus hazañas heroicas durante la guerra."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:65
msgid ""
"We ventured further southwards into more uncharted territory. Our few adepts "
"sensed traces of the sword's power further south. After two whole days, we "
"stumbled upon a valley, enshrouded in a thick eerie mist..."
msgstr ""
"Seguimos avanzando más al sur, en territorio completamente desconocido. "
"Nuestras pocas adeptas percibían rastros del poder de la espada más al sur. "
"Tras dos días enteros, dimos con un valle envuelto en una espesa niebla "
"inquietante…"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:71
msgid ""
"Facing so many vampires... This might have been the most intense battle of "
"my life. The retrieval excursion of the Wild Lands during my training years "
"was intense, but it was nowhere near as gruesome as this battle."
msgstr ""
"Enfrentar a tantos vampiros… Tal vez fue la batalla más intensa de mi vida. "
"La expedición de recuperación en las Tierras Salvajes durante mis años de "
"entrenamiento fue dura, pero no se compara con lo brutal que fue esta."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:73
msgid ""
"As our forces clashed against the vampires, we could almost feel their "
"murderous intent. Slashing one down, two more would take its place. They "
"craved our blood. It was a miracle how we survived the night and managed to "
"force their retreat."
msgstr ""
"Cuando nuestras fuerzas chocaron contra los vampiros, casi podíamos sentir "
"su intención asesina. Derribabas a uno y dos más ocupaban su lugar. Deseaban "
"nuestra sangre. Fue un milagro que sobreviviéramos la noche y lográramos "
"obligarlos a retroceder."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:75
msgid ""
"We finally caught the glimpse of a fortress in the mountains. Our sacred "
"sword was being held there and we had to retrieve it. We did not know what "
"we would be facing there. We were driven by just one thing, our oath to the "
"village which was to retrieve the sword. We found an abandoned fort nearby "
"and decided to use it to rally for the battle..."
msgstr ""
"Al fin divisamos una fortaleza en las montañas. Allí tenían nuestra espada "
"sagrada y teníamos que recuperarla. No sabíamos a qué nos enfrentaríamos, "
"pero solo nos impulsaba una cosa: nuestro juramento al pueblo de traer la "
"espada de vuelta. Encontramos un fuerte abandonado cerca y decidimos usarlo "
"para reagruparnos antes de la batalla…"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:81
msgid ""
"To think we would get the opportunity to fight alongside Lord Ryuuma of "
"House Shimotsuki himself. What an honour! My old buddies at the Aeranas "
"training barracks would never believe me if I told them this."
msgstr ""
"Pensar que tendríamos la oportunidad de luchar junto al mismísimo señor "
"Ryuuma de la Casa Shimotsuki… ¡Qué honor! Mis viejos compañeros del cuartel "
"de entrenamiento en Aeranas nunca me creerían si se los contara."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:83
msgid ""
"The appearance of dwarves and the valefolk inside the fortress and being "
"allied with the mages was disturbing. The Valefolk have not been seen in "
"almost a century and yet, there were here now."
msgstr ""
"La aparición de enanos y habitantes del valle dentro de la fortaleza, "
"aliados con los magos, era inquietante. A los habitantes del valle no se los "
"había visto en casi un siglo y, sin embargo, ahí estaban."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:85
msgid ""
"Lord Ryuuma was disturbed as well. He ordered the fortress to be searched "
"thoroughly for any clues or informations of this development. We discovered "
"a hidden trap door at the rear of the fortress. It was not before Lord "
"Ryuuma summoned us to the chamber underneath the fortress..."
msgstr ""
"El señor Ryuuma también estaba preocupado. Ordenó registrar la fortaleza a "
"fondo en busca de pistas sobre este acontecimiento. Descubrimos una "
"trampilla oculta en la parte trasera. Poco después, el señor Ryuuma nos "
"convocó a la cámara bajo la fortaleza…"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:91
msgid ""
"We had retrieved the Electrifyre! Our village's heirloom is back in our "
"position. Although the great hero, Shimotsuki Ryuuma, had offered us to join "
"him in his quest to investigate the Valefolk involvement, we decided it was "
"best to just return back to the village."
msgstr ""
"¡Recuperamos la Electryfire! La reliquia de nuestro pueblo volvió a estar en "
"nuestras manos. Aunque el gran héroe Shimotsuki Ryuuma nos ofreció "
"acompañarlo en su misión para investigar la participación de los habitantes "
"del valle, decidimos que lo mejor era regresar al pueblo."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:93
msgid ""
"The return journey to the village was relatively uneventful. We did face "
"more vampires again, but by employing a proper stratagem we quickly overcame "
"them. Once we had returned to the village, the Electrifyre was placed in his "
"shrine. As a lesson learnt, we have placed even more guards for the shrine "
"to prevent further occurences of robbery."
msgstr ""
"El viaje de regreso al pueblo fue relativamente tranquilo. Sí nos topamos "
"otra vez con vampiros, pero con una buena estrategia los vencimos rápido. Al "
"llegar al pueblo, la Electryfire volvió a su santuario. Aprendimos la "
"lección y ahora hay más guardias para evitar que vuelva a ocurrir un robo."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:95
msgid ""
"The village was overjoyed with the restoration of the Electrifyre and its "
"shrine. A grand feast was held for this occassion. The coming days in the "
"village were uneventful. As the militia, we returned to just patroling and "
"maintaining vigilance. A part of me wondered what would have happened if we "
"did decide to accompany Lord Ryuuma into the Depths. Would destiny have "
"turned out differently?"
msgstr ""
"El pueblo se llenó de alegría con la restauración de la Electryfire y su "
"santuario. Se celebró un gran banquete por la ocasión. Los días siguientes "
"en el pueblo fueron tranquilos. Como milicia, volvimos a patrullar y "
"mantener la vigilancia. Una parte de mí se preguntaba qué habría pasado si "
"hubiéramos decidido acompañar al señor Ryuuma a las Profundidades. ¿El "
"destino habría sido distinto?"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:99
msgid ""
"Maybe I could have gotten more opportunites to participate in an epic war if "
"it ever came and make a name for myself. I guess I shall never know."
msgstr ""
"Tal vez habría tenido más oportunidades de participar en una guerra épica y "
"hacerme un nombre. Supongo que nunca lo sabré."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:105
msgid ""
"With Lord Ryuuma leading the way, our band of moderately battle-hardened "
"village militia descended into the depths. The dark tunnel extended on and "
"on. It felt nearly endless until we saw a light source in the distance..."
msgstr ""
"Con el señor Ryuuma al frente, nuestro grupo de milicianos del pueblo —ya "
"algo curtidos en batalla— descendió a las profundidades. El túnel oscuro se "
"extendía sin fin. Parecía interminable hasta que vimos una fuente de luz a "
"lo lejos…"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:114
msgid ""
"Encountering a remnant delusional Jinn within the depths of the land was not "
"somthing we were expecting. It was a brutal ordeal but we had prevailed in "
"the end. After the Jinn was vanquished or temporarily put to rest (we were "
"not sure what the outcome really meant), we continue our trek and entered "
"another vast cavern. It was a sight to behold..."
msgstr ""
"Encontrar a un jinn delirante y residual en las profundidades no era algo "
"que esperáramos. Fue una prueba brutal, pero al final vencimos. Después de "
"derrotar al jinn (o de dormirlo temporalmente, no estábamos seguros), "
"seguimos avanzando y entramos en otra enorme caverna. Era un espectáculo "
"impresionante…"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:123
msgid ""
"Navigating through the 'mushroom forest,' if you can call it that, was a "
"relentless endeavour. We fought a multitude of creatures ranging from "
"venomous scorpions to endless spawning Mudcrawlers."
msgstr ""
"Atravesar el «bosque de hongos» (si se le puede llamar así) fue un esfuerzo "
"sin descanso. Luchamos contra multitud de criaturas, desde escorpiones "
"venenosos hasta reptadores de barro que aparecían sin parar."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:125
msgid ""
"Like in the Jinn cavern, we had encountered the valefolk here again. The "
"valefolk were clearly coming in considerable numbers to reclaim their "
"fortress. One fact that Lord Ryuuma found concerning is that their dwarven "
"allies were not seen with them in either of the two encounters. Where could "
"they have gone?"
msgstr ""
"Al igual que en la caverna del jinn, volvimos a encontrarnos con habitantes "
"del valle. Venían en gran número para recuperar su fortaleza. Algo que "
"preocupaba al señor Ryuuma era que sus aliados enanos no aparecieran en "
"ninguno de los dos encuentros. ¿Dónde podrían estar?"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:127
msgid ""
"We continued on our march. Soon we reached a nexus of cave tunnels going in "
"various directions..."
msgstr ""
"Seguimos marchando. Pronto llegamos a un cruce de túneles que se dirigían en "
"varias direcciones…"

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:145
msgid ""
"Despite heavy losses, we had managed to collapse and seal off the entrance "
"to the Valefolk city. Although it would have been better to disrupt what "
"ritual the Valefolk were attempting to execute, we did not have the strength "
"necessary to overcome their well erected defenses. With the entrance "
"collapsed, the Valefolk would not be able to mount an offensive on us for "
"the considerable future."
msgstr ""
"A pesar de las grandes pérdidas, logramos derrumbar y sellar la entrada a la "
"ciudad de los habitantes del valle. Habría sido mejor interrumpir el ritual "
"que intentaban realizar, pero no teníamos la fuerza necesaria para superar "
"sus sólidas defensas. Con la entrada colapsada, no podrán atacarnos en un "
"futuro cercano."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:147
msgid ""
"We bade farewell to our Deep Elven allies and returned to the surface. Now, "
"we had retrieved the Electrifyre! Moreover, we had the honour of fighting "
"alongside one of the Kingdom's greatest swordsmen, Shimotsuki Ryuuma. His "
"feats during the southern war had been the talk of the town for many a "
"month. To think, we commonfolk had the opportunity to participate in an epic "
"quest with him."
msgstr ""
"Nos despedimos de nuestros aliados elfos profundos y regresamos a la "
"superficie. ¡Habíamos recuperado la Electryfire! Además, tuvimos el honor de "
"luchar junto a uno de los mejores espadachines del Reino, Shimotsuki Ryuuma. "
"Sus hazañas en la guerra del sur habían sido la comidilla durante meses. "
"Pensar que nosotros, gente común, tuvimos la oportunidad de participar en "
"una búsqueda épica con él."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:149
msgid ""
"Afterwards, we returned to our village. Surprisingly, Lord Shimotsuki and "
"his regiment offered to accompany us. This was reassuring as their mere "
"presence would stave off the vampires."
msgstr ""
"Después regresamos al pueblo. Sorprendentemente, el señor Shimotsuki y su "
"regimiento se ofrecieron a acompañarnos. Eso era tranquilizador, porque su "
"mera presencia mantendría alejados a los vampiros."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:152
msgid ""
"The village was overjoyed with the restoration of the Electrifyre and its "
"shrine. A grand feast was held for this occassion. Lord Shimotsuki and his "
"soldiers even stayed for a fornight and trained some of us for more "
"proficient combat. He felt that the Aragwaithi should stay ever vigilant to "
"be a beacon of leadership and hope in the wake of some new cataclysm."
msgstr ""
"El pueblo se llenó de alegría con la restauración de la Electryfire y su "
"santuario. Se celebró un gran banquete. El señor Shimotsuki y sus soldados "
"se quedaron una quincena y entrenaron a algunos de nosotros para combatir "
"mejor. Él consideraba que los Aragwaithi debían mantenerse siempre alerta "
"para ser un faro de liderazgo y esperanza ante cualquier nuevo cataclismo."

#. [story]
#: Electrifyre/macros/story.cfg:154
msgid ""
"Several months later, a scout from Aeranas arrived with a summons for me to "
"the Northern city. I made no delays and ventured forth immediately. A week "
"later, I found myself entering the Royal Gardens at Aeranas..."
msgstr ""
"Varios meses después, un explorador de Aeranas llegó con una convocatoria "
"para mí a la ciudad del norte. No perdí tiempo y partí de inmediato. Una "
"semana después me encontré entrando en los Jardines Reales de Aeranas…"

